args: Louise has become the latest to join the ranks\nof those at the Halidom.
*sigh* I wonder what Lowen is doing\nright now?
She is quite overprotective of her\nyounger brother, Lowen.
Blast, I'm worrying about him AGAIN!
He's grown up now, which means I can't\ncontinue to be the clingy older sister.
I need something in my life beyond just\nworrying after Lowen.
Ah, there you are, Louise. I could use your\nhelp with something, if that's all right?
Funny enough, I was just looking for\nsomething to help me while away the\nhours. How can I help?
Well, our housework seems to be in\nsomething of a backlog.
Unfortunately, I have to clean the\nstoreroom today and don't have time\nto play catch-up.
I'm happy to help; living with Lowen has\nlet me master all manner of chores!
Well, if you'd be so kind as to take care of\nthe laundry, dishes, and tidying the dining\nhall, I'd be most grateful.
Leave it to me. Perhaps I'll start with the\nlaundry, since there's clearly no shortage\nof it.
But with a little wind magic on my side,\nit will be dried in a jiffy. Off I go!
Done with the laundry, are you? Excellent.\nNext, you can take care of the dish—
Huh? No, I mean I'm DONE done.\nEverything around here is clean as\na pile of fresh new whistles.
To thank you, I will prepare your\nfavorite dish for dinner.
Louise? You appear severely perplexed.\nIs something the matter?
All right, that's enough fiend\nextermination for one day.
'Bout time! My axe arm is startin' to throb.
It's been three days since we left the\nHalidom. This was quite the journey.
Yes, and I appreciate all your efforts.\nWe'll be sure to take a couple of days to\nrest when we get back to the castle.
Wait, an actual day off? Hell yeah!\nI'm gonna sleep like a cat and eat\nlike a pig, then do it all over again!
Perhaps I'll finally have time to read\nthat new novel I purchased.
And I will take the opportunity to do a bit\nof painting.
Downtime is important if we're not going\nto burn ourselves out. But what about you,\nLouise? Any big plans?
I guess there isn't anything I want to do.
I mean there's simply no activity that I\nparticularly enjoy or wish to take part in.
I fight and do various household tasks,\nbut beyond that...
Hmm. You had the same reaction a few\ndays ago when I asked your favorite meal.

To be honest, I've never had to consider
such things; my entire life has been spent
looking after Lowen and making sure his
needs were taken care of.
Huh. Ain't that a kinda unhealthy way\nfor a person to live?
Once the little bro takes off, yer gonna be\nleft swingin' in the breeze.
This is a truth I'm slowly coming to grips\nwith. Clearly I must learn how to prioritize\nmy own life.
That's good to hear. Life is certainly more\nfun when you have hobbies and interests\nthat make you happy.
I'm sure Lowen would want you to be\nhappy, right?
Yes, of course you're right. I must discover\nwho Louise really is.
I'm going to take this opportunity to sever\nmy dependence on Lowen and focus on\nmyself!
The search for the new Louise starts now!
Looks like the wind is at my back now.\nAll right, Louise, it's time to prove you're\nmore than just a dependable archer...
It's time to find the new me!
